column5: The battery might be permanently damaged or faulty, resulting in it not holding a charge. Possible causes include battery degradation over time, exposure to extreme temperatures, internal short circuits, or charger/charging port issues.

column4: Battery dead and cannot be charged
column5: If your battery is dead and cannot be charged, first try using a different charger or charging cable to rule out a faulty charger. Check the charging port for any debris or damage. If the problem persists, the battery or the device's charging circuitry might be faulty and may need professional repair or replacement.

column4: Battery dead and cannot be charged
column5: If your battery is dead and cannot be charged, the issue may be due to a faulty battery, charger, charging port, or power source. First, try using a different charger and power outlet to rule out those possibilities. If the battery is removable, try reseating it or testing with a new battery. If the device still does not charge, it may require professional repair or battery replacement.

column4: Battery dead and cannot be charged
column5: If your battery is dead and cannot be charged, the issue could be due to a faulty battery, charger, charging port, or internal hardware problems. First, try using a different charger and cable to rule out charger issues. If the battery is removable, try reseating or replacing it. If these steps don't work, the battery may need to be replaced or the device checked by a technician.

To resolve this, first verify your payment information and check your bank account balance. If everything seems correct, try the transaction again or contact your bank to understand if there are any holds or restrictions on your account.

Sorry you're seeing a payment failure — that can be caused by several common issues (insufficient funds, card expiry, billing info mismatch, bank decline, temporary gateway outage, 3D Secure/OTP not completed). I can help troubleshoot, but I need a couple of details: which service or merchant were you paying, the exact error message shown (or a screenshot), and the time of the attempt. Do NOT share full card numbers or CVV — you can share the card’s last 4 digits and any transaction ID if available.

Sorry you ran into a payment failure. Common causes are expired card, incorrect card details or billing address, insufficient funds, a bank block or 3D Secure/OTP step that wasn’t completed, temporary gateway issues, or a typing/network error. Try the troubleshooting steps below and, if those don’t work, contact your bank or the merchant with the transaction reference shown in the app or email.
